     <div type="to_the_reader">
   <pb facs="2"/>
   <pb facs="2"/>
   <head>To the Christian Rea<g ref="char:EOLhyphen"/>der, health.</head>
   <p>
      <hi>
         <seg rend="decorInit">I</seg> Doe heere</hi> present vnto thy fauorable viewe (most curteous and gentle Rea<g ref="char:EOLhyphen"/>der) thys little Pamphlet, which wanting a particular Pa<g ref="char:EOLhyphen"/>tron, commeth as it were, a beg<g ref="char:EOLhyphen"/>ging vnto thee, for no lesse then thy whole selfe, and that cheef<g ref="char:EOLhyphen"/>lie for thine owne good, the way to protect it, is to direct thy life by it, and to suffer it to possesse thee, as soone as thou hast pos<g ref="char:EOLhyphen"/>sest it: which if thou be so hap<g ref="char:EOLhyphen"/>pie to accomplish, it will teach
<pb facs="3"/>
thee to winne loue by feare: life by death: yea, euerlasting hap<g ref="char:EOLhyphen"/>pines, by the transitory trouble<gap reason="illegible" resp="#pdcc" extent="1 letter">
         <desc>•</desc>
      </gap> of this wretched world: and to giue it iust praise in a word, it i<gap reason="illegible" resp="#pdcc" extent="1 letter">
         <desc>•</desc>
      </gap> a worke of the learned and spi<g ref="char:EOLhyphen"/>rituall <hi>Granada,</hi> aptly transla<g ref="char:EOLhyphen"/>ted into English.</p>
   <closer>
      <signed>L A</signed>
   </closer>
